parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OCS to detect a passenger can lead to the deactivation of the passenger airbag, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger airbag is not enabled
the "Passenger Airbag OFF" telltale is illuminated
the airbag sensor turns off and on while driving depending on how the passenger sits
the airbag sensor does not detect the passenger if they are seated improperly
cross their legs
or recline the seat too far back.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loss of Traction Control and Stability in High Regeneration Mode
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of traction control, stability controls, and anti-lock braking systems in high regeneration mode can cause the vehicle to become uncontrollable, especially in low-traction situations, posing a significant risk to the driver and others on the road.
symptoms: Vehicle aquaplanes
loss of traction
skidding
and uncontrolled movement; ABS and traction control systems fail to engage; vehicle feels like it has locked all four wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high voltage battery can cause the vehicle to enter "turtle mode" at highway speeds, reducing power and speed, and potentially leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Vehicle enters "turtle mode" at highway speeds
loss of power
reduced speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's lane departure system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly changes lanes or accelerates without driver input
making it difficult to maintain control
and potentially leading to collisions or near-miss incidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or slide, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially on inclined surfaces.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls or slides while parked
even with the parking brake engaged
and may only lock two wheels
leaving the other two wheels free to roll.
